answer:
**Margin vs Padding:**
- **Margin**: Space outside the element (between elements)
- **Padding**: Space inside the element (between content and border)

**Individual Margins:**
```css
.box {
    margin-top: 20px;
    margin-left: 15px;
    margin-right: 10px;
    margin-bottom: 25px;
}
```

**One Line Margin:**
```css
.box {
    margin: 20px;           /* All sides */
    margin: 10px 20px;      /* top/bottom left/right */
    margin: 10px 20px 15px; /* top left/right bottom */
    margin: 10px 20px 15px 5px; /* top right bottom left */
}
```

**Zero Margin:**
```css
.no-margin {
    margin: 0px; /* Border will touch edge of website */
}
```

**Font Family with Fallbacks:**
```css
p {
    color: red;
    font-family: "Arial", "Helvetica", sans-serif;
}

h1 {
    font-family: "Times New Roman", "Times", serif;
}

.code {
    font-family: "Consolas", "Monaco", "Courier New", monospace;
}
```

**Why use multiple fonts:**
- If first font isn't available, browser tries the next one
- Ensures text displays even if preferred font fails to load
- Provides consistent appearance across different systems

**Font Properties:**
```css
p {
    font-style: italic;        /* normal, italic, oblique */
    font-weight: bold;         /* normal, bold, 100-900 */
    font-size: 18px;           /* px, em, rem, % */
}

h1 {
    font-style: normal;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 2.5em;
}
```

**Shorthand:**
```css
.text {
    font: italic bold 16px Arial, sans-serif;
}
```

**Text Decoration Options:**
```css
.underline {
    text-decoration: underline;
}

.overline {
    text-decoration: overline;
}

.line-through {
    text-decoration: line-through;
}

.dotted-underline {
    text-decoration: cyan dotted underline;
}

.wavy-underline {
    text-decoration: red wavy underline;
}

.no-decoration {
    text-decoration: none;
}
```

**Centering with Auto Margins:**
```css
.center {
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
    width: 300px;
}

.left {
    margin-left: 0;
    margin-right: auto;
}

.right {
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: 0;
}
```

**Note:** Setting both left and right to auto makes div stay in the middle regardless of browser size.

**Float Property:**
```css
img {
    float: left;    /* Takes all images to top left */
}

img {
    float: right;   /* Takes images to top right */
}

.clear {
    clear: both;    /* Stops floating elements */
}
```

**Popular for wrapping text around images:**
- `float: left` - Element floats to left, text wraps around right
- `float: right` - Element floats to right, text wraps around left
- `clear: left/right/both` - Stops elements from floating

**Text Alignment:**
```css
.center {
    text-align: center;
}

.left {
    text-align: left;
}

.right {
    text-align: right;
}

.justify {
    text-align: justify;
}
```

**Inline CSS:**
```html
<h1 style="text-align: center;">Centered Heading</h1>
<p style="text-align: right;">Right-aligned paragraph</p>
```

**External CSS:**
```css
h1 { text-align: center; }
p { text-align: justify; }
```

**Clear Property:**
```css
.float-left {
    float: left;
}

.clear-left {
    clear: left;
}

.clear-both {
    clear: both;
}

.clear-right {
    clear: right;
}
```

**If float: left, use:**
- `clear: left` - Stops left-floating elements
- `clear: both` - Stops all floating elements

**If float: right, use:**
- `clear: right` - Stops right-floating elements
- `clear: both` - Stops all floating elements

**Relative Position:**
```css
.relative {
    position: relative;
    top: 50px;
    left: 50px;
}
```

**Relative Position:**
- Element positioned relative to its normal position
- `top`, `left`, `right`, `bottom` properties work
- Original space is preserved (other elements don't move)
- Element moves from its original position
- Useful for fine-tuning element placement

**Absolute Position:**
```css
.absolute {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
}
```

**Absolute Position:**
- Element positioned relative to nearest positioned ancestor
- If no positioned ancestor, positioned relative to document body
- Removed from normal document flow
- Other elements act as if it doesn't exist
- `top`, `left`, `right`, `bottom` properties work
- Used for overlays, modals, tooltips

**Fixed Position:**
```css
.fixed {
    position: fixed;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
}
```

**Fixed Position:**
- Element positioned relative to viewport (browser window)
- Stays in same position when scrolling
- Removed from normal document flow
- `top`, `left`, `right`, `bottom` properties work
- Used for navigation bars, chat buttons, back-to-top buttons
- Always visible regardless of scroll position

**CSS Animations with Keyframes:**
```css
@keyframes myslide {
    from { margin-left: 100px; }
    to { margin-left: 0px; }
}

@keyframes myrotate {
    100% { transform: rotateZ(360deg); }
}

@keyframes myopacity {
    100% { opacity: 0; }
}

@keyframes mycolorchange {
    20% { background-color: red; }
    40% { background-color: orange; }
    60% { background-color: yellow; }
    80% { background-color: blue; }
    100% { background-color: purple; }
}

.animated {
    animation: myslide 3s linear 0s infinite running;
}
```

**Animation Properties:**
- `animation-name` - Name of keyframe
- `animation-duration` - How long animation lasts
- `animation-iteration-count` - How many times to repeat
- `animation-timing-function` - Speed curve
- `animation-delay` - Delay before starting

