**CSS Background Image Properties - Complete Guide**

**🎨 Individual Properties (Detailed Control):**
```css
.element {
    background-image: url('my-background.jpg');
    background-position: center;
    background-size: cover;
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    background-attachment: fixed;
    background-color: #f0f0f0;
}
```

**⚡ Background Shorthand (Concise):**
```css
.element {
    background: url('image.jpg') center/cover no-repeat fixed #f0f0f0;
}
```

**🔧 Property Breakdown:**

**1. Background Image & Sources:**
```css
.single-image {
    background-image: url('photo.jpg');
}

.multiple-images {
    background-image: url('pattern.png'), url('main-bg.jpg');
}

.gradient {
    background-image: linear-gradient(to right, red, blue);
}
```

**2. Background Positioning:**
```css
.center {
    background-position: center;      /* Perfect center */
}

.custom {
    background-position: 20px 50px;   /* X Y coordinates */
}

.percentage {
    background-position: 75% 25%;     /* Percentage based */
}

.multiple-positions {
    background-position: top left, bottom right; /* For multiple images */
}
```

**3. Background Sizing Options:**
```css
.cover {
    background-size: cover;           /* Fills container, may crop */
}

.contain {
    background-size: contain;         /* Fits entire image, no crop */
}

.specific {
    background-size: 300px 200px;     /* Exact dimensions */
}

.auto {
    background-size: auto;            /* Natural image size */
}

.multiple-sizes {
    background-size: cover, contain;  /* For multiple images */
}
```

**4. Background Repeating:**
```css
.no-repeat {
    background-repeat: no-repeat;     /* Single instance */
}

.repeat {
    background-repeat: repeat;        /* Tile in both directions */
}

.repeat-x {
    background-repeat: repeat-x;      /* Horizontal tiling only */
}

.repeat-y {
    background-repeat: repeat-y;      /* Vertical tiling only */
}

.space {
    background-repeat: space;         /* Evenly distribute */
}
```

**5. Background Attachment:**
```css
.fixed {
    background-attachment: fixed;     /* Stays in place during scroll */
}

.scroll {
    background-attachment: scroll;    /* Scrolls with content (default) */
}

.local {
    background-attachment: local;     /* Scrolls with element's content */
}
```

**🎯 Practical Examples:**

**Hero Section Background:**
```css
.hero {
    background: url('hero-bg.jpg') center/cover no-repeat fixed #000;
    height: 100vh;
}
```

**Pattern Background:**
```css
.pattern {
    background: url('pattern.png') center/auto repeat;
}
```

**Gradient Overlay:**
```css
.overlay {
    background: 
        linear-gradient(rgba(0,0,0,0.5), rgba(0,0,0,0.5)),
        url('background.jpg') center/cover;
}
```

**📋 Shorthand Syntax Order:**
```
background: [color] [image] [position] / [size] [repeat] [attachment] [origin] [clip];
```

**Example with all properties:**
```css
.full-shorthand {
    background: #fff url('image.jpg') center/cover no-repeat fixed padding-box content-box;
}
```

**💡 Key Notes:**
- **Gradients** don't repeat by default
- **Multiple backgrounds** are layered from first (top) to last (bottom)
- **Shorthand resets** any unspecified properties to their defaults
- **Use individual properties** for better readability in complex scenarios
- **Test background-attachment: fixed** on mobile devices as support varies

**Performance Tip:** Use `background-size: cover` carefully with large images as it can impact performance on mobile devices.

